                    </div>
                    <span>I watched this movie because I was dating a guy who is a huge Ewan MacGregor fan. I have always liked his performances, but I thought that this one was exceptional.  It tells the story of a failed writer who has a mysterious past with a woman that he abandoned. He works on a barge and begins an affair with his bosses' wife. It sort of is a mystery, but when it all comes down to it, this movie is basically an excuse to show as much sex as possible.(I have no objection to this!) There isn't a lot of dialogue, its more of what's not said that's important, and the story isn't really fast-paced, but if you get into to feeling of it, its actually pretty good.(One of my few objections is having to look at Tilda Swinton's hairy armpit. Yuck!) Basically to top it all off, not-so-nice people in Scotland have lots of sex and you get to see plenty of Ewan MacGregor in the process.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">What a waste!</div>
